    <h2>ROLLING 7-DAY SCORE & SELF-CARE BONUS:</h2>
    <div class="scoring">
        <p>The 7-day score provides an overview of your functioning and self-care efforts over the past week.</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Sum of Daily Scores:</strong> This is the total of your daily scores from the last 7 days.</li>
            <li><strong>Self-Care Bonus:</strong> You get <span class="bonus">+1 point</span> for each self-care activity you engaged in during the last 7 days:
                <ul>
                    <li>Got hair done</li>
                    <li>10 mins to self</li>
                    <li>Coloured in</li>
                    <li>Made music</li>
                    <li>Completed assessments</li>
                    <li>Other self-care activities you note</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li><strong>Consistency Bonus:</strong> If your daily total score was positive for 5 or more days in the last 7 days, add an extra <span class="bonus">+2 points</span>.</li>
            <li><strong>TOTAL 7-DAY SCORE:</strong> This is the sum of your daily scores plus your self-care bonus points and the consistency bonus (if applicable).</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <h2>WHAT THE SCORES MEAN (General Guidelines):</h2>
    <div>
        <h3>Daily Score:</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Positive Score:</strong> More tasks completed and maintained than not done (includes +1 for meaningful conversation if applicable).</li>
            <li><strong>Around Zero:</strong> Balance between completed and uncompleted tasks.</li>
            <li><strong>Negative Score:</strong> More tasks not completed or undone, indicating potential difficulties.</li>
            <li><strong>Significantly Negative Score:</strong> May be a "Red Flag" indicating a need for support.</li>
        </ul>
        <h3>7-Day Score:</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Higher Positive Score:</strong> Generally good level of functioning and self-care over the week, with consistent positive days.</li>
            <li><strong>Score Around Zero:</strong> Mixed week.</li>
            <li><strong>Negative Score:</strong> More challenging week.</li>
            <li><strong>Track Trends:</strong> Look at the pattern of your 7-day scores over time.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

